content:
You can call Data Mappers using Apex or a REST API. You can also use custom input and output and environment variables in Data Mappers.

Omnistudio Data Mapper REST API
You can invoke any type of Data Mapper using the Data Mapper REST API. To update Salesforce objects, issue a POST request that includes a JSON payload that is formatted to comply with the input that the Data Mapper load expects. To retrieve data from Salesforce, issue a GET call to a Data Mapper Extract, specifying the Id or parameters identifying the data to be retrieved.

Omnistudio Data Mapper Calls From Apex
To call a Data Mapper from Apex, call the vlocity_ins.DRGlobal.processObjectsJSON() method, specifying the name of the Data Mapper and the input data that it requires.

DRGlobal Class and Methods
The DRGlobal class provides multiple methods for calling Omnistudio Data Mappers from Apex.

Environment Variables in Omnistudio Data Mappers and Integration Procedures
You can use environment variables to define Default Values and Filter Values, and in Formulas.

Custom Input and Output for Omnistudio Data Mappers in OmniStudio
By default, Data Mappers handle JSON and XML data. To handle other data formats, you can configure a Data Mapper to use a custom input or output that you implement is a custom class.
